.hero
	.cell
		h2.page-title Contributing
			small.block So you'd like to help out?

.row

	.columns.large-6.large-centered(data-contains-toc)
		p.
			Sure thing. I'm always happy to accept help, however let's keep it tidy yeah?
		p.
			Check out the sections below to see where your efforts can best be applied.

		h4(id="how-to-contribute", data-toc-entry) How to contribute
		ol
			li Head over to the <a href="{{ WinterSmith.pkg.npm.bugs.url }}">Issue Tracker</a> and pick out an open ticket.
			li Clone the repo, get it up and running on your local machine
			li Deal with the ticket and in your final commit message include something like: `Fixes #234`, where 234 is the issue id.
			li push it to your repo
			li make a pull request from your repo to the develop branch of this repo.

		p Mostly you'll need a <a href="https://github.com/join">github account</a>, which is free.

		h5(id="code-contributions", data-toc-entry) Pull Requests

		p I'll be placing priority on these types of contributions

		ol
			li Clone the repo
			li Make changes, Limit changes to one feature/fix per pull request or it will be rejected.
			li Submit a <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YTbRzhQju4c">pull request</a>

		h5(id="issues", data-toc-entry) Issues

		ol
			li Head over to the <a href="{{ WinterSmith.pkg.npm.bugs.url }}">issue tracker</a>
			li Write a brief description
			li explain concisely the contribution
			li submit it!

